"kind":"attribute"},{"text":"(memberAttribute) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"macro","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DebugDescription","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This macro converts compatible description implementations written in Swift"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to an LLDB format known as a Type Summary. A Type Summary is LLDB’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"equivalent to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":", with the distinction that it does not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"execute code inside the debugged process. By avoiding code execution,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"descriptions can be produced faster, without potential side effects, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shown in situations where code execution is not performed, such as the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"variable list of an IDE."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider this an example. This "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Team"},{"type":"text","text":" struct has a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"summarizes some key details, such as the team’s name. The debugger only"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"computes this string on demand - typically via the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"po"},{"type":"text","text":" command. By applying"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DebugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" macro, a matching Type Summary is constructed. This"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allows the user to show a string like “Rams [11-2]”, without executing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":". This improves the usability, performance, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"reliability of the debugging experience."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@DebugDescription","struct Team: CustomDebugStringConvertible {","   var name: String","   var wins, losses: Int","","   var debugDescription: String {","       \"\\(name) [\\(wins)-\\(losses)]\"","   }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DebugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" macro supports both "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"description"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as well as a third option: a property named "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lldbDescription"},{"type":"text","text":". The first"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"two are implemented when conforming to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomDebugStringConvertible"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomStringConvertible"},{"type":"text","text":" protocols. The additional "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lldbDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property is useful when both "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"description"},{"type":"text","text":" are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implemented, but don’t meet the requirements of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DebugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macro. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lldbDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" is implemented, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DebugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" choose it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"over "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"description"},{"type":"text","text":". Likewise, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"debugDescription"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"preferred over "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"description"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Description Requirements","level":3,"anchor":"Description-Requirements","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The description implementation has the following requirements:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The body of the description implementation must a single string"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"expression. String concatenation is not supported, use string interpolation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instead."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"String interpolation can reference stored properties only, functions calls"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and other arbitrary computation are not supported. Of note, conditional"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"logic and computed properties are not supported."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Overloaded string interpolation cannot be used."}]}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swift\/debugdescription()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"Swift-PageImage-card.png":{"alt":"An orange Swift logo on a gradient background.","identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card@2x.png","traits":["2x","light"]},{"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card~dark@2x.png","traits":["2x","dark